tspan.tspan: We are new born and drop onto this sphere
a simple act that causes a cascade
our lived effects deepening year on year.
Each scene flickers past in heady parade
its rare a restful moment one might find
to ponder on the patterns we have made.
Tumbling down the slopes of the daily grind
our sand-dune paths sometimes feel misaligned.
though you must admit, some clouds are silvered:
For an ordered life that's safely filtered
is dull: revel in being bewildered.
